org.mundo.util.plugins
Class PluginManager

java.lang.Object
  org.mundo.util.plugins.PluginManager
All Implemented Interfaces:
IDirectoryMonitor.IDirectoryModification
public class PluginManager
extends java.lang.Object
implements IDirectoryMonitor.IDirectoryModification

A PluginManager monitors a given directory for plugins. Plugins which are dropped there are newly registered to the system. Plugins which are deleted are unregistered from the system. The files for dropped plugins may remain locked in the future - currently they are not locked.

Author:
AHa

Method Detail

addPluginHandler

public static void addPluginHandler(IPluginMonitor.IPluginHandler handler,
                                    java.io.File directory)
                             throws java.io.IOException
Adds a PluginHandler monitoring a given directory. Initially, the handler gets registrations for all plugin files already residing in the directory. After that, modifications in the directory are automatically reflected. There may be multiple pluginHandlers for a directory and/or namespace. The order in which the pluginRegistered/pluginUnRegistered methods of these handlers are called is not defined.

Parameters:
handler - plugin handler for the PluginManager
directory - the directory to look for plugins
Throws:
java.io.IOException - if directory is no valid directory

removePluginHandler

public static void removePluginHandler(IPluginMonitor.IPluginHandler handler,
                                       java.io.File directory,
                                       boolean notifyUnload)
Removes a PluginHandler that was monitoring the directory. If the handler was registered for monitoring the directory, it will be removed. Other directories monitored by the handler are not affected. If the handler was not monitoring the given directory, the method does nothing.

Parameters:
handler - plugin handler for the PluginManager
directory - the directory to stop investigating
notifyUnload - if true, the pluginUnRegistered method of the unloaded handler will be called.

fileAdded

public void fileAdded(java.io.File directory,
                      java.io.File file)
Monitors the PluginManager's directory for newly added JAR-Files. A new JAR file is read and its classes get loaded into the system. This method is supposed to be called from the DirectoryMonitor only.
